-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP: African Minerals, Kloeckner
-- 
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 04:16AM EDT
-- None



Oct 8 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Bayer and London Mining, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * African Minerals <AMIq.L>, London Mining <LOND.L>: Jefferies cuts to hold from buy * Kloeckner <KCOGn.DE>: JP Morgan cuts to neutral from overweight; target to 11 euros Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Actelion Ltd <ATLN.VX>: UBS removes from most preferred list in European bio & medtech * African Minerals <AMIq.L>: Jefferies cuts to hold * African Minerals <AMIq.L>: Jefferies cuts price target to 17p * Bayer <BAYGn.DE>: Morgan Stanley raises target to 113 euros from 109 euros; equal weight * Burberry <BRBY.L>: Barclays raises price target to 1585p from 1550p; rating equal weight * Hikma Pharmaceuticals <HIK.L>: UBS adds to most preferred list in European bio & medtech * Kloeckner <KCOGn.DE>: JP Morgan cuts to neutral from overweight * Kloeckner <KCOGn.DE>: JP Morgan cuts price target to 11 euros from 12.50 euros * London Mining <LOND.L>: Jefferies cuts to hold from buy; cuts price target to 5p